$b'$ and $c'$, followed by\ncollisions of species of interest especially those with known $\\beta_2$ but\nunknown $\\gamma$. The results demonstrate the unique opportunities offered by\nhigh-energy collisions as a tool to perform interdisciplinary nuclear physics\nstudies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 1 Sep 2021 20:27:20 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 12 Apr 2022 21:29:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-05-04"}
