 that obtained in the\nfirst scenario, and also the channels $B^+ \\to a_0^+(1950) \\left[ K^+{\\bar\nK}^0/\\pi^+\\eta \\right] K^0$ whose branching fractions are linear dependent on\nthe partial width $\\Gamma_{a_0(1950) \\to KK/\\pi\\eta}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 2 Sep 2021 01:34:47 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 8 Sep 2021 13:48:01 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 16 Oct 2021 02:11:01 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 10 Jan 2022 07:23:33 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-03-02"}
